PAST MEDICAL HISTORY
1.  Elevated cholesterol.  She has had mildly elevated cholesterol and is on fish oil which has improved her numbers.  She has not been recommended to be on a statin.
2.  History of elevated blood pressure without hypertension.  She says occasionally this has been elevated, but she has not been recommended to be on medication.
3.  Overweight.
PAST SURGICAL HISTORY
1.  She underwent a tubal ligation to one of her fallopian tubes, and then she had the removal of one of her ovaries and the fallopian tube.  This was approximately 30 years ago.  She also had an appendectomy then.
2.  History of thyroid biopsy 20 years go which was normal.  She had never been on thyroid medication or had subsequent problems.

